  "prompt": "Has Quora become less popular?",
  "response": "As of 2023, Quora remains a popular platform for asking and answering questions, but its prominence and user engagement have evolved over time. Several factors may contribute to perceptions that it has become less popular:\n\n1. **Rise of Competitors**: Platforms like Reddit, Twitter (with Spaces and threads), and specialized forums have grown in popularity, offering similar or more dynamic ways to engage with communities or seek information.\n\n2. **Content Moderation Issues**: Quora has faced criticism for inconsistent content moderation, including spam, low-quality answers, and misinformation, which has alienated some users.\n\n3. **Algorithm Changes**: Changes in Quora\u2019s algorithm and monetization strategies (e.g., promoting Quora+ or paywalled content) have frustrated some users, leading to reduced engagement.\n\n4. **Decline in User Experience**: Some users feel the platform has become overly commercialized, with an increase in ads and promoted content detracting from the quality of the experience.\n\n5. **Shift in User Behavior**: The rise of video-based platforms like TikTok and YouTube has shifted user preferences toward visual and short-form content, which is not Quora\u2019s primary focus.\n\nThat said, Quora still has a significant user base, particularly for niche topics or detailed, long-form answers. It continues to be a valuable resource for many, but its influence may not be as dominant as it once was in the broader social media and Q&A landscape.",
